Police have arrested three men accused of murdering a Zimbabwean man working on a popular game farm in Kei Mouth just outside East London. The incident happened two weeks ago.Vanhukwavo Kuka, 47, was found dead in a guard house situated on the farm.East London police spokeswoman Warrant Officer Hazel Mqala confirmed the incident, saying police had opened a murder case.For the full story get a copy of the Dispatch or subscribe to our e-Edition for the complete newspaper with jobs, classifieds, crosswords, TV schedules and back editions.